    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-19T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-19T08:00:00-05:00" n="672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–1944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pinkerton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-19T16:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 19, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>153. Arab reaction to recent American statements on Palestine<note n="19"
                        xml:id="d672fn19">See letter from President Roosevelt to Senator Wagner,
                        October 15, <hi rend="italic">supra;</hi> for statements by Governor Thomas
                        E. Dewey and others, see footnotes 21 and 24, <ref target="#pg_617">pp.
                            617</ref> and <ref target="#pg_618">618</ref>, respectively.</note> has
                    been heretofore restricted to rather mild newspaper editorials and private
                    conversations protesting against them. There have been no organized protests.
                    Yesterday afternoon, however, Arab Chamber of Commerce canceled appointment with
                    Culbertson Mission<note n="20" xml:id="d672fn20">For correspondence regarding
                        the Special Economic Mission to the Middle East, headed by William S.
                        Culbertson, see <ref target="#pg_38">pp. 38</ref> ff.</note> members now
                    visiting Palestine and said, “We would like this action of the Chamber to be
                    read as a protest against the President’s pronouncement, and as a sign of our
                    unlimited disappointment.” Mission left this morning for Haifa, Tel Aviv and
                    Jaffa where it expects to meet Jewish and Arab organizations and upon its return
                    I will report as to its reception in those cities. Mr. Culbertson himself has
                    not yet arrived in Palestine.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pinkerton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
